        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 14 at 6:16PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 615 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hurricane Harbor Splashtown, or near Spring, moving north at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Southeastern Conroe, Tomball, Pinehurst, The Woodlands, Greater
Greenspoint, Spring, Aldine, Oak Ridge North, Shenandoah, Magnolia,
Woodloch, Bush Intercontinental Airport, The Woodlands Pavillion,
Hooks Airport, Chateau Woods, Willowbrook, Hurricane Harbor
Splashtown, and Greater Inwood.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
